section.def:
Chairperson (主席)
            means the Chairperson of the Authority appointed under section 2 of Schedule
                3;

committee (委員會), in
            relation to the Authority, means a committee of the Authority established under
                section 23(1) or (2) of Schedule 3;

company (公司) has the
            meaning given by section 2(1) of the Companies Ordinance (Cap. 622) and includes—(a)a body corporate incorporated or established by or under any other
                    Ordinance; and(b)a body corporate incorporated or established outside Hong Kong;

member (成員), in relation
            to the Authority, means a member of the Authority appointed under section 2 of
                Schedule 3;

owners’ organization (業主組織), in relation to a property, means an organization
            (whether or not formed under the Building Management Ordinance (Cap. 344) or a deed of mutual covenant) that is authorized to act on behalf
            of all the owners of the property;

property management company (物業管理公司) means a business entity (whether a company,
            partnership or sole proprietorship) that carries on the business of providing property
            management services;

subparagraph.content:
whether, in the 5 years before the relevant application, the individual
                        has entered into a composition or scheme of arrangement with the
                        individual’s creditors;

whether the individual is a mentally disordered person, or a patient,
                        within the meaning of section 2(1) of the Mental Health Ordinance
                            (Cap. 136);

whether the individual has been convicted of a criminal offence (other
                        than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

whether the individual is or was the sole proprietor of a property
                        management company whose application for a PMC licence has been refused or
                        whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

whether the individual is or was an officer of, or a partner in, a
                        property management company whose application for a PMC licence has been
                        refused or whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

whether, in the 5 years before the relevant application, the company
                        has entered into a composition or scheme of arrangement with its
                        creditors;

whether the company has been convicted of a criminal offence (other
                        than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

whether every director of the company is a suitable person to be
                        associated with the company’s business of providing property management
                        services;

whether, in the 5 years before the relevant application, any partner in
                        the partnership has entered into a composition or scheme of arrangement with
                        the partner’s creditors;

whether any partner in the partnership is a mentally disordered person,
                        or a patient, within the meaning of section 2(1) of the Mental
                        Health Ordinance (Cap. 136);

whether any partner in the partnership has been convicted of a criminal
                        offence (other than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

whether any partner in the partnership is or was the sole proprietor of
                        a property management company whose application for a PMC licence has been
                        refused or whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

paragraph.content:
whether the individual is a mentally disordered person, or a patient,
                    within the meaning of section 2(1) of the Mental Health Ordinance
                        (Cap. 136);

whether the individual is or was the sole proprietor of a property
                    management company whose application for a PMC licence has been refused or whose
                    PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

subparagraph.content:
whether, in the 5 years before the relevant application, the director
                        has entered into a composition or scheme of arrangement with the director’s
                        creditors;

whether the director is a mentally disordered person, or a patient,
                        within the meaning of section 2(1) of the Mental Health Ordinance
                            (Cap. 136);

whether the director has been convicted of a criminal offence (other
                        than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

whether the director is or was the sole proprietor of a property
                        management company whose application for a PMC licence has been refused or
                        whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

whether the director is or was an officer of, or a partner in, a
                        property management company whose application for a PMC licence has been
                        refused or whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

whether, in the 5 years before the relevant application, the director
                        has entered into a composition or scheme of arrangement with the director’s
                        creditors;

whether the director has been convicted of a criminal offence (other
                        than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

paragraph.content:
if the PMC is neither incorporated under the Companies Ordinance (Cap. 622) nor incorporated under a former Companies
                    Ordinance, the date on which the PMC commences business, as stated in the PMC’s
                    application for registration under the Business Registration Ordinance (Cap. 310);

if the PMC is a company, the conviction record of the PMC (if any) in
                    relation to disciplinary offences or criminal offences under this
                    Ordinance;

the fees payable for the extension of the validity of a licence under
                        section 10(11)(b) or
                        (12)(b);

to receive and consider any material, whether by way of oral evidence,
                    written statements, documents or otherwise, and whether or not the material
                    would be admissible in civil or criminal proceedings;

to receive and consider any material, whether by way of oral evidence,
                    written statements, documents or otherwise, and whether or not the material
                    would be admissible in civil or criminal proceedings;

for a person who is a licensee, may make any of the orders described in
                        section 26(1)(a), (b), (e) and (f) against the person;
                    or

section.def:
Collector (署長)
                        means the Collector of Stamp Revenue appointed under section 3 of
                        the Stamp Duty Ordinance (Cap. 117);

payment period (繳款限期), in relation to the levy payable for a leviable
                        instrument, means the period within which the levy is payable under
                                section 54(3);

subparagraph.content:
if the levy is paid later than 1 month but not later than 2 months
                        after the expiry of the payment period, 4 times the amount of the levy;
                        or

paragraph.content:
whether the applicant is a mentally disordered person, or a patient,
                        within the meaning of section 2(1) of the Mental Health Ordinance
                            (Cap. 136);

whether the applicant has been convicted of a criminal offence (other
                        than an offence under this Ordinance) involving fraud or
                        dishonesty;

whether the applicant is or was the sole proprietor of a property
                        management company whose application for a PMC licence has been refused or
                        whose PMC licence has been revoked or suspended;

the information to be contained in, and the documents to accompany, an
                        application for a provisional PMP (Tier 1) licence or provisional PMP (Tier
                        2) licence;

may include criteria relating to the applicant’s academic
                        qualifications, professional qualifications and relevant work experience;
